# The board. What is SAID travels; what is RUNNING here does not.
# An allowlist on purpose: this folder holds pids and read-positions, so anything
# new stays ignored until someone lets it out deliberately.
*
!.gitignore
!.gitattributes
# The ledger: merge-safe (stable ids + per-origin ord + union merge), so it can be
# shared across machines. See the design note at the top of arc-board.js.
!notes.jsonl
# NOT origin.json — it is what makes two clones distinguishable. Share it and both
# write under one origin, ord diverges per clone, and cursors silently skip notes.
# NOT cursor-*/claim-*/anchor — a read position and a pid are true on ONE machine.
